<p>Above, <a href="https://www.cmc.edu/academic/faculty/profile/lars-schmitz">Lars Schmitz</a>, a professor at Claremont McKenna College,&nbsp;guides us “through a giant tree of life mapping the evolution of eyes in the animal kingdom: how they work, why they’ve taken the form they have, and the evolutionary advantages they’ve unlocked across species.” The video comes courtesy of <em>Wired</em>. It’s 36 minutes and downright fascinating.</p>
